How is blood not very appropriate in league of legends {{champion:8}} 
I believe both Katarina and Talon have blood animations on dots and Vlad turns into a giant pool of blood so how is having a giant blood jelly monster inappropriate in the least? in a game where you're stabbing, poisoning, burning, electrocuting, blowing up and even drowning people in this game with skills honestly... 

if you're proving anything it's that Riot screwed up with not being at all creative with any of Zac's current skins, pool party at least they added some creative aspects with the shorts and goggles that make it worth more than just a chroma but honestly it's just a blue recolour for the most part.. how hard is it to make anything with a mushy consistency into an actually good Zac skin? then again that would require more effort than just recoloring something that's already been made so..
